<promed@promedmail.org>
[The articles specify the birds are negative for West Nile virus and some
other encephalopathies. It would be nice to know which other
encephalopathies were tested for, whether Avian Vacuolar Myelinopathy was
tested for, and what histopathology was done. Without more information
regarding pathology or tests performed, it is difficult to establish a list
of possible differential diagnoses. - Mod.TG]
